### Upload Service — REST Client test file
### Requires VS Code extension: REST Client (humao.rest-client)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   1. cd infra && docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.yml up -d postgres minio rabbitmq
###   2. pnpm nx run upload-service:serve
###
### Auth: service trusts X-User-Id set by gateway — no JWT needed here

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8086
@userId  = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@userId2 = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000002

# Set this to a jobId returned from the upload request
@jobId = REPLACE_WITH_JOB_ID

###
### ─── HEALTH ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [1] Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###
### ─── UPLOAD ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [2] Upload a track (any authenticated user)
### Change the file path below to a real audio file on your machine
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

My Test Track
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="genre"

POP
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.mp3"
Content-Type: audio/mpeg

< ./test.mp3
------Boundary--

### [3] Upload — no auth (expects 401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="title"

No Auth
------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.mp3"
Content-Type: audio/mpeg

< ./test.mp3
------Boundary--

### [4] Upload — missing title (expects 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----Boundary

------Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.mp3"
Content-Type: audio/mpeg

< ./test.mp3
------Boundary--

###
### ─── LIST JOBS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [5] List all jobs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [6] List jobs — filter by status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs?status=TRANSCODING&page=1&size=10
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [7] List jobs — pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs?page=1&size=5
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [8] List jobs — no auth (expects 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs

###
### ─── JOB DETAIL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [9] Get job by ID (replace @jobId above first)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [10] Get job — not found (expects 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [11] Get job owned by another user (expects 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId2}}

###
### ─── RETRY ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [12] Retry a FAILED job
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}/retry
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [13] Retry — non-FAILED job (expects 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}/retry
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

###
### ─── CANCEL ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### [14] Cancel a job
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}/cancel
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### [15] Cancel already-cancelled job (expects 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/upload/jobs/{{jobId}}/cancel
X-User-Id: {{userId}}
